						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīrachōḷadēva: Year 21 = 1203-04 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged. It appears to record a gift of land in Vīranārāyaṇa-chaturvēdimaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēya,</hi> in Vaikāvi-nāḍu, to the god Vīrachōḷa-īśvaramuḍaiyār in Koḻumam. One of the boundaries of the land is stated to be <hi rend="italic">Chēraṉai-mēṉkoṇḍa-chōḻaṉ-peruvadi</hi> (road ?).</p>						

						</summary>
